extends ../layout.pug
block extradependencies
    link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/KaTeX/0.7.1/katex.min.css")
    script(src='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/KaTeX/0.7.1/katex.min.js')

block pagetitle
    title A Prisoner and a King

block title
    div(class='container')
        h1 A Prisoner and a King
        p(class='subtitle text-center') A King decides to give a prisoner a chance of being set free. The king places two boxes, 15 white, and 15 black balls on the table. The prisoner can distribute the balls between two boxes in any way with the only constraint that no box is empty. After this, the king picks one of the boxes with probability 1/2 each, and picks a random ball from that box (each ball is picked with equal probability). If the ball happens to be white, then the prisoner is freed. Distribute the balls between the two boxes to maximize prisonerâ€™s chances.

block container
    div(class='center text-center padded content sums-table')
        table(class='table table-bordered table-striped')
            thead
                tr
                    th
                    th First box
                    th Second box
            tbody
                tr
                    td White balls
                    td
                        input(type='number', id='whitefirst')
                    td
                        input(type='number', id='whitesecond')
                tr
                    td Black balls
                    td
                        input(type='number', id='blackfirst')
                    td
                        input(type='number', id='blacksecond')

    p(class='center text-center')
        button(type='button', id='btncheck' class='btn btn-default') Check

    div(class='modal fade', id='check_modal', tabindex='-1')
        div(class='modal-dialog')
            div(class='modal-content')
                div(class='modal-body')
                    p Here is the analysis of the situation:
                    ul
                        li The probability that the king picks the first box is &nbsp;
                            span(id='spanprobfirstbox')
                        li The probability that the king picks the second box is &nbsp;
                            span(id='spanprobsecondbox')
                        li
                            span There are&nbsp;
                            span(id='spannumballsfirstbox')
                            span &nbsp; balls in the first box, thus, the probability to draw any particular ball from the first box is &nbsp;
                            span(id='spanballfirstbox')
                        li The same rationale gives us that a particular ball is drawn from the second box with probability &nbsp;
                            span(id='spanballsecondbox')
                        li
                            span There are&nbsp;
                            span(id='spannumwhiteballsfirstbox')
                            span &nbsp; white balls in the first box and &nbsp;
                            span(id='spannumwhiteballssecondbox')
                            span &nbsp; white balls in the second box. The probability to draw a white ball is equal to the sum of probabilities over all white balls: &nbsp;
                            span(id='spantotal')
                    p(id='ultimatecomment')
                div(class='modal-footer')
                    button(type='button', class='btn btn-default', data-dismiss='modal') Close

block append scripts
    script(src='/javascripts/quiz/prisoner-and-king.js')

